# Vite Conventions (apps)

## Environment variables

- Prefix: `VITE_*` only (exposed to client)
- Read in `src/lib/env.ts`; never `import.meta.env` scattered in components
- Declare in `src/vite-env.d.ts`:

```typescript
interface ImportMetaEnv {
  readonly VITE_APP_NAME: string;
  readonly VITE_API_BASE_URL: string;
}
```

- Document every var in `.env.example`

## Static assets

| Location | Use for |
|----------|---------|
| `public/` | `robots.txt`, favicon, files needing fixed URL (`/logo.png`) |
| `src/assets/` | Imported assets (hashed by Vite: `import logo from "@/assets/logo.svg"`) |

## Dev servers

- H5: port **5173** (`apps/h5/vite.config.ts`)
- Web: port **5174** (`apps/web/vite.config.ts`)

## API bootstrap

- `src/lib/api.ts` creates singleton via `createApi()` from `@ryx/api`
- Pages import `getApi()` — not `createApi` directly
